    "body": "I'm getting the same issue - so I checked /etc/hosts yesterday and saw a `::1 localhost` entry.  Removing the entry and restarting `npx hardhat node` seemed to work.\r\n\r\nHowever today when starting hardhat network I'm getting the same issue and I cannot see a `::1 localhost` entry in /etc/hosts - not too sure where it's getting this entry now.\r\n\r\nI'm using MacOS Catalina 10.15.7, node version 17.0.1.\r\n\r\n/etc/hosts looks like (now):\r\n\r\n```\r\n##\r\n# Host Database\r\n#\r\n# localhost is used to configure the loopback interface\r\n# when the system is booting.  Do not change this entry.\r\n##\r\n127.0.0.1       localhost\r\n255.255.255.255 broadcasthost\r\n# Added by Docker Desktop\r\n# To allow the same kube context to work on the host and the container:\r\n127.0.0.1 kubernetes.docker.internal\r\n# End of section\r\n```\r\n\r\nExpected result is:\r\n\r\n```\r\nStarted HTTP and WebSocket JSON-RPC server at http://127.0.0.1:8545/\r\n```",
